# childwaf blocklist – Custom / User-defined Domains
#
# Add any domains here that don't fit the built-in categories.
# Reference this list in a child profile with:
#   BLOCK_CATEGORIES="... custom"
#
# Format:
#   - One domain per line
#   - Subdomains are covered automatically (e.g. "example.com" also blocks
#     "www.example.com", "sub.example.com", etc.)
#   - Lines beginning with # are comments
#   - Inline comments are also supported:  example.com  # reason

# ── Add your custom entries below ─────────────────────────────────────────────

